<paragraph id="680036C151797257189EFE03D21DFDDE" blockId="26.[151,731,465,525]" box="[151,529,500,525]" pageId="26" pageNumber="63">
(Pls 2C, 3K, 4K, 6C, 7K; 
<figureCitation id="F0842A445179725719B1FE03D204FDDE" box="[440,520,500,525]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="26.[151,250,1881,1903]" captionTargetBox="[179,1391,859,1858]" captionTargetId="figure@26.[179,1391,859,1858]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 13. Lordiphosa hamatispina sp. nov. (A−M: holotype 06027). A, B, sex-combs on right foreleg (lateral and ventral view, respectively); C, D, periphallic organs (caudal and caudolateral view, respectively); E, epandrial ventral lobe (lateral view); F, ventroapical spine of cercus (lateral view); G, surstylus and ventral spines of cercus (caudal view); H, inner surface of surstylus (caudolateral view); I, 10th sternite (ventral view); J̅L, phallic organs (ventral, ventrolateral, and lateral view, respectively); M, apical shape of paramere (lateral view)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439547/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="63">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
