<subSubSection id="20A5654A51797257189EFDCBD59AFCFE" pageId="26" pageNumber="63" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="680036C151797257189EFDCBD59AFCFE" blockId="26.[151,1436,572,813]" pageId="26" pageNumber="63">
<emphasis id="5ACBEAD351797257189EFDCBD11DFD87" bold="true" box="[151,273,572,597]" pageId="26" pageNumber="63">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Male foreleg with sex-combs composed of blackish brown, thick, apically blunt teeth on 1st to 3rd tarsomeres: transverse, but irregular, rows densely covering nearly entire lengths of 1 
<taxonomicName id="AFBF4D42517972571C85FD97D4DBFDAA" box="[1164,1239,607,632]" pageId="26" pageNumber="63" rank="subSpecies" subSpecies="and">st and</taxonomicName>
2nd tarsomeres; transverse rows not clearly separated from each other, rather oblique on proximal portion of 1 
<taxonomicName id="AFBF4D42517972571CA6FD73D533FD4E" box="[1199,1343,644,668]" pageId="26" pageNumber="63" rank="subSpecies" subSpecies="tarsomere">st tarsomere</taxonomicName>
; 1 distal transverse row of 3 teeth on 3rd tarsomere (
<figureCitation id="F0842A44517972571A83FD50D301FD12" box="[650,781,679,704]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="26.[151,250,1881,1903]" captionTargetBox="[179,1391,859,1858]" captionTargetId="figure@26.[179,1391,859,1858]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 13. Lordiphosa hamatispina sp. nov. (A−M: holotype 06027). A, B, sex-combs on right foreleg (lateral and ventral view, respectively); C, D, periphallic organs (caudal and caudolateral view, respectively); E, epandrial ventral lobe (lateral view); F, ventroapical spine of cercus (lateral view); G, surstylus and ventral spines of cercus (caudal view); H, inner surface of surstylus (caudolateral view); I, 10th sternite (ventral view); J̅L, phallic organs (ventral, ventrolateral, and lateral view, respectively); M, apical shape of paramere (lateral view)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439547/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="63">Fig. 13A,B</figureCitation>
). Cercus ventrally tapered, with a fringe of 6–7 spines on ventrosubapical margin (
<figureCitation id="F0842A445179725719BDFD3BD25EFD36" box="[436,594,716,741]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="26.[151,250,1881,1903]" captionTargetBox="[179,1391,859,1858]" captionTargetId="figure@26.[179,1391,859,1858]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 13. Lordiphosa hamatispina sp. nov. (A−M: holotype 06027). A, B, sex-combs on right foreleg (lateral and ventral view, respectively); C, D, periphallic organs (caudal and caudolateral view, respectively); E, epandrial ventral lobe (lateral view); F, ventroapical spine of cercus (lateral view); G, surstylus and ventral spines of cercus (caudal view); H, inner surface of surstylus (caudolateral view); I, 10th sternite (ventral view); J̅L, phallic organs (ventral, ventrolateral, and lateral view, respectively); M, apical shape of paramere (lateral view)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439547/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="63">Fig. 13C,D,G</figureCitation>
) and largest, apically hook-like curved spine at ventral apex (
<figureCitation id="F0842A44517972571D21FD3BD59CFD36" box="[1320,1424,716,741]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="26.[151,250,1881,1903]" captionTargetBox="[179,1391,859,1858]" captionTargetId="figure@26.[179,1391,859,1858]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 13. Lordiphosa hamatispina sp. nov. (A−M: holotype 06027). A, B, sex-combs on right foreleg (lateral and ventral view, respectively); C, D, periphallic organs (caudal and caudolateral view, respectively); E, epandrial ventral lobe (lateral view); F, ventroapical spine of cercus (lateral view); G, surstylus and ventral spines of cercus (caudal view); H, inner surface of surstylus (caudolateral view); I, 10th sternite (ventral view); J̅L, phallic organs (ventral, ventrolateral, and lateral view, respectively); M, apical shape of paramere (lateral view)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439547/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="63">Fig. 13F</figureCitation>
). Paramere distally thin, strongly curved ventrad and outward, medially slightly sinuate (
<figureCitation id="F0842A44517972571C7CFD18D4F8FCDA" box="[1141,1268,751,776]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="26.[151,250,1881,1903]" captionTargetBox="[179,1391,859,1858]" captionTargetId="figure@26.[179,1391,859,1858]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 13. Lordiphosa hamatispina sp. nov. (A−M: holotype 06027). A, B, sex-combs on right foreleg (lateral and ventral view, respectively); C, D, periphallic organs (caudal and caudolateral view, respectively); E, epandrial ventral lobe (lateral view); F, ventroapical spine of cercus (lateral view); G, surstylus and ventral spines of cercus (caudal view); H, inner surface of surstylus (caudolateral view); I, 10th sternite (ventral view); J̅L, phallic organs (ventral, ventrolateral, and lateral view, respectively); M, apical shape of paramere (lateral view)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439547/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="63">Fig. 13J–L</figureCitation>
), apically with minute bifurcation (
<figureCitation id="F0842A4451797257197FFCE3D1EFFCFE" box="[374,483,788,813]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="26.[151,250,1881,1903]" captionTargetBox="[179,1391,859,1858]" captionTargetId="figure@26.[179,1391,859,1858]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 13. Lordiphosa hamatispina sp. nov. (A−M: holotype 06027). A, B, sex-combs on right foreleg (lateral and ventral view, respectively); C, D, periphallic organs (caudal and caudolateral view, respectively); E, epandrial ventral lobe (lateral view); F, ventroapical spine of cercus (lateral view); G, surstylus and ventral spines of cercus (caudal view); H, inner surface of surstylus (caudolateral view); I, 10th sternite (ventral view); J̅L, phallic organs (ventral, ventrolateral, and lateral view, respectively); M, apical shape of paramere (lateral view)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439547/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="63">Fig. 13M</figureCitation>
). Gonopods dorsally not concaved, slightly curved dorsad in lateral view (
<figureCitation id="F0842A44517972571D2DFCE3D584FCFE" box="[1316,1416,788,813]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="26.[151,250,1881,1903]" captionTargetBox="[179,1391,859,1858]" captionTargetId="figure@26.[179,1391,859,1858]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 13. Lordiphosa hamatispina sp. nov. (A−M: holotype 06027). A, B, sex-combs on right foreleg (lateral and ventral view, respectively); C, D, periphallic organs (caudal and caudolateral view, respectively); E, epandrial ventral lobe (lateral view); F, ventroapical spine of cercus (lateral view); G, surstylus and ventral spines of cercus (caudal view); H, inner surface of surstylus (caudolateral view); I, 10th sternite (ventral view); J̅L, phallic organs (ventral, ventrolateral, and lateral view, respectively); M, apical shape of paramere (lateral view)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439547/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="63">Fig. 13L</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
