<subSubSection id="20A5654A5178725618CEFF60D595FD7A" pageId="27" pageNumber="64" type="description">
<paragraph id="680036C15178725618CEFF60D481FEED" blockId="27.[151,1437,151,1149]" pageId="27" pageNumber="64">
<emphasis id="5ACBEAD35178725618CEFF60D15EFF62" bold="true" box="[199,338,151,176]" pageId="27" pageNumber="64">Description</emphasis>
(characters commonly seen in 
<taxonomicName id="AFBF4D42517872561AA2FF6ED30AFF7D" authority="Katoh &amp; Zhang &amp; Toda &amp; Zhang &amp; Gao, 2018" authorityName="Katoh &amp; Zhang &amp; Toda &amp; Zhang &amp; Gao" authorityYear="2018" box="[683,774,152,176]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Lordiphosa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yangi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="5ACBEAD3517872561AA2FF6ED2B6FF62" box="[683,698,153,176]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="64">L</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="5ACBEAD3517872561AC1FF6FD30AFF7D" box="[712,774,152,175]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="64">yangi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="41F857A8517872561B04FF60D36AFF62" box="[781,870,151,176]" pageId="27" pageNumber="64" rank="species">
<emphasis id="5ACBEAD3517872561B04FF60D36AFF62" bold="true" box="[781,870,151,176]" pageId="27" pageNumber="64">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
not repeated) (
<specimenCount id="7EB9FD48517872561C07FF6FD429FF62" box="[1038,1061,152,176]" pageId="27" pageNumber="64" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
). Head (Pls 2C, 3K, 4K, 6C, 7K): Frontal vitta yellowish brown. Fronto-orbital plate dark grayish yellow, anteriorly yellowish brown. Ocellar triangle dark grayish yellow. Occiput dark brown, dorsomedially yellowish brown. Supracervical setulae 16̄17 per side; postocular setae 13–15 per side. Clypeus pale grayish yellow. Cibarium with 19¯23 medial and 16 posterior sensilla per side. Prementum with 4–5 (1 proximal, 1–2 lateral, and 2 distal) pairs of setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="680036C15178725618CEFEBBD59FFE5A" blockId="27.[151,1437,151,1149]" pageId="27" pageNumber="64">Thorax (Pl. 2C) yellowish brown. Mesonotum medially with 1 brown, longitudinal, anteriorly indistinct, caudally broadened stripe. Scutellum medially brown. Mid katepisternal seta distinctly longer than those below it.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="680036C15178725618CEFE62D523FE7E" blockId="27.[151,1437,151,1149]" box="[199,1327,404,429]" pageId="27" pageNumber="64">
Legs (Pl. 2C, 
<figureCitation id="F0842A4451787256196BFE63D1EFFE7E" box="[354,483,404,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="26.[151,250,1881,1903]" captionTargetBox="[179,1391,859,1858]" captionTargetId="figure@26.[179,1391,859,1858]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 13. Lordiphosa hamatispina sp. nov. (A−M: holotype 06027). A, B, sex-combs on right foreleg (lateral and ventral view, respectively); C, D, periphallic organs (caudal and caudolateral view, respectively); E, epandrial ventral lobe (lateral view); F, ventroapical spine of cercus (lateral view); G, surstylus and ventral spines of cercus (caudal view); H, inner surface of surstylus (caudolateral view); I, 10th sternite (ventral view); J̅L, phallic organs (ventral, ventrolateral, and lateral view, respectively); M, apical shape of paramere (lateral view)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439547/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="64">Fig. 13A,B</figureCitation>
): Midleg 1 
<taxonomicName id="AFBF4D42517872561A50FE63D2E8FE7E" box="[601,740,404,428]" pageId="27" pageNumber="64" rank="subSpecies" subSpecies="tarsomere">st tarsomere</taxonomicName>
longer than total length of 4 succeeding tarsomeres.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="680036C15178725618CEFE40D590FE02" blockId="27.[151,1437,151,1149]" box="[199,1436,439,464]" pageId="27" pageNumber="64">Abdomen (Pl. 2C): Tergites grayish brown, glossy, caudally with dark grayish brown, narrow, marginal bands.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="680036C15178725618CEFE2BD3D4FDEF" blockId="27.[151,1437,151,1149]" pageId="27" pageNumber="64">
Male terminalia (
<figureCitation id="F0842A44517872561999FE2BD22FFE26" box="[400,547,476,501]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="26.[151,250,1881,1903]" captionTargetBox="[179,1391,859,1858]" captionTargetId="figure@26.[179,1391,859,1858]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 13. Lordiphosa hamatispina sp. nov. (A−M: holotype 06027). A, B, sex-combs on right foreleg (lateral and ventral view, respectively); C, D, periphallic organs (caudal and caudolateral view, respectively); E, epandrial ventral lobe (lateral view); F, ventroapical spine of cercus (lateral view); G, surstylus and ventral spines of cercus (caudal view); H, inner surface of surstylus (caudolateral view); I, 10th sternite (ventral view); J̅L, phallic organs (ventral, ventrolateral, and lateral view, respectively); M, apical shape of paramere (lateral view)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439547/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="64">Fig. 13C–M</figureCitation>
): Epandrium with ca. 27 long setae per side. Cercus with ca. 22 long setae. Surstylus caudally with a row of ca. 12 prensisetae on caudodorsal margin and 23–29 recurved setae on ventral portion of inner surface. Aedeagal apodeme slightly longer than aedeagus.
</paragraph>
